The Tossers are a seven-piece celtic punk band from Chicago. They formed in the early &#039;90s and have started to move into the spotlight recently, having toured with such bands as Lost City Angels, Murphy&#039;s Law, Streetlight Manifesto, Catch 22, Dropkick Murphys and most recently The Reverend Horton Heat. They opened for The Pogues in New York City on St. Patrick&#039;s Day 2007. Having formed in the early 90s, the band pre-dates more well-known Celtic Punk bands such as the aforementioned Dropkick Murphys and Flogging Molly, which formed in 1995 and 1997 respectively.
